{"TopicId":208587,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"How I can get long thin struts like this?","CreatedByName":"1000sowy","CreatedById":221801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-14T04:59:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"1000sowy","CreatedById":221801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-14T04:59:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been watching Nessus\u0027 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/9Y6C_LWAGDE?t=192\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Evideo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(timestamped), and I\u0027ve really liked these long thin struts and attaching \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters on them. I\u0027ve tried the mods on description but none of them seems to have it. Do you know a mod has something like this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bEus9J3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022107.39\u0022 height=\u0022305\u0022 width=\u0022284\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/bEus9J3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-14T05:01:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/221801-1000sowy/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022221801\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/221801-1000sowy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@1000sowy\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:happy:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022:happy:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYour question has been moved from KSP Discussions to Add-on Discussions, the corner of the forum to ask mod related questions.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeadJohn","CreatedById":201293,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-14T13:22:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBluedog Design Bureau (BDB) has some \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E arms like that. The ones I\u0027m thinking of fold for launch then get extended in orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-14T15:01:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose seem to be from sxt\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dci","CreatedById":106864,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-15T13:44:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlace \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters block directly on probe body, use offset tool to move them to desired position and connect with struts as usual. They are not necessary, but looks much better, than thruster block floating in the open air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}